An '''assignment cover sheet''' is a paper used by [[student]]s when completing [[assignment (education)|assignment]]s at [[university]] for their courses. These coversheets generally contain [[metadata]] about the assignment (such as the name of the student and the course number). This aids the efficient handling of assignments. Other types of data may be included, depending on the needs of the course.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mendota.english.wisc.edu/~WAC/page.jsp?id=44&c_type=category&c_id=27 |title=Integrating Writing Into Your Course |author= |date= |work=University of Wisconsin (Madison) |accessdate=October 7, 2010 }}{{dead link|date=July 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>

Some universities require and/or provide cover sheets in standardized formats. These are often in the form of computer files which a student can download, print, and personalize.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://assessment.illinoisstate.edu/generaleducation/coversheet.shtml |title=Student Assignment CoverSheet |author= |date= |work=Illinois State University |accessdate=October 7, 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101127035002/http://assessment.illinoisstate.edu/generaleducation/coversheet.shtml |archivedate=November 27, 2010 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.unisa.edu.au/ltu/students/study/assessment/use_coversheet.asp |title=Using the assignment cover sheet |author= |date=June 10, 2010 |work=University of South Australia |accessdate=October 7, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.education.monash.edu.au/students/current/resources/assigncoversheet.html |title=Assignment cover sheet |author= |date= |work=Monash University |accessdate=October 7, 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110219020616/http://www.education.monash.edu.au/students/current/resources/assigncoversheet.html |archivedate=February 19, 2011 }}</ref>

Cover sheets are also required by some educational entities that are not universities.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pclab.cccoe.k12.ca.us/assignme.htm |title=Assignment Sheets |author= |date= |work=Contra Costa County Office of Education Regional Occupation Program |accessdate=October 7, 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090426133217/http://pclab.cccoe.k12.ca.us/assignme.htm |archivedate=April 26, 2009 }}</ref>

