'''Las Caritas''' ("The faces") is a collection of [[Indigenous peoples of the Americas|Indian]] inscriptions in a rock formation looking out over [[Lake Enriquillo]] in the [[Dominican Republic]]. The place is also called the '''Trono de Enriquillo''' ("Enriquillo's throne") because it is said the [[Taíno people|Taíno]] leader [[Enriquillo]] used to camp here during his rebellion.

