{{Infobox film | name = The Alice Faye Collection | image = | caption = DVD cover | border = no | country = United States | language = English | producer = Various | production companies = [[20th Century Fox]] | distributor = [[20th Century Fox Home Entertainment]] | budget = | gross = }} '''''The Alice Faye Collection''''' is a [[DVD]] [[box set#Video|box set]] with four movies of the famous 30's and 40's film star [[Alice Faye]].
It is part of the 20th Century Fox Marquee Musicals, that refers to a collection of films released on DVD by [[Twentieth Century-Fox]].
== Background == In December 2007, [[20th Century Fox Home Entertainment|Fox Home Entertainment]] have announced the release of "The Alice Faye Collection" for February 20, 2007 as part of their 20th Century Fox Marquee Musicals series of releases.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thedigitalfix.com/film/content/63543/lillian-russell-1940|title=THE ALICE FAYE COLLECTION IN FEBRUARY|publisher=The Digital Fix|accessdate=6 June 2017}}</ref>
== Films == {| class="wikitable sortable" |- ! Film Title ! Main cast ! Director ! Original Release Year |- | ''[[On the Avenue]]'' | [[Dick Powell]], [[Madeleine Carroll]] | [[Irving Berlin]] | 1937 |- | ''[[Lillian Russell (film)|Lillian Russell]]'' | [[Don Ameche]], [[Henry Fonda]] | [[Irving Cummings]] | 1940 |- | ''[[That Night in Rio]]'' | [[Don Ameche]], [[Carmen Miranda]] | [[Irving Cummings]] | 1941 |- | ''[[The Gang's All Here (1943 film)|The Gang's All Here]]'' | [[Carmen Miranda]], [[Phil Baker (comedian)|Phil Baker]], [[Benny Goodman]] | [[Busby Berkeley]] | 1943 |- |}
== Reception == The ''[[New York Times]]'' says, "20th Century Fox Home Entertainment has been turning out some first-rate discs lately, but something has gone horribly wrong with “The Alice Faye Collection,”<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2007/02/20/movies/20dvd.html|title=New DVDs: The Cuban Masterworks Collection|publisher=[[The New York Times]]|accessdate=6 June 2017}}</ref> ''[[San Diego Reader]]'' wrote that "The Alice Faye Collection has four of the great Fox musical star's best films: On the Avenue, Lillian Russell, That Night in Rio, and The Gang's All Here. My favorites are the last two because they are brightened by the Brazilian bombshell Carmen Miranda. Miss Faye exuded the charm and innocence our boys were fighting for in [[World War II]]."<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sandiegoreader.com/news/2007/nov/01/funny-face-meet-me-st-louis-alice-faye-collection/#|title=Funny Face, Meet Me in St. Louis, The Alice Faye Collection|publisher=[[San Diego Reader]]|accessdate=6 June 2017}}</ref>
